FBIS4-15115 "drsov067_g_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 WESTERN REGION Belarus Slavic Assembly Terms UN World `Gendarme' Slavic Assembly Terms UN World `Gendarme' WS0704092794 Minsk BTK Television Network in Belarusian 1800 GMT 6 Apr 94 WS0704092794 Minsk BTK Television Network Belarusian BFN [Text] The Slavic Assembly Belaya Rus wrote a letter to UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali who is staying in Minsk in which it expressed its concern over the fact that the UN is being transformed from a peacekeeping organization to a world judge and gendarme. It has become common for the UN to use a dual approach toward resolving international conflicts, the letter reads. The UN is becoming a conductor of wishes of a narrow group of states with the United States at the top. The Slavic Assembly demanded that violent interference in the life of the peoples of Yugoslavia be halted. The letter [passage indistinct] an aggression against Iraq and murder of Somalia citizens were initiated. [words indistinct] Military interference with the affairs of some states and indulgence to other states become key mechanisms of the UN activities.
